Reference-contexts: In this context correct means conforming to the IEEE Standard 754, and a big first step was to decide exactly what the specification required. The IEEE document is partly reliant on the meaning of natural language requirements; Geoff Barrett's recasting of the Standard into the Z specification language <ref> [1] </ref> is unambiguous and serves as the touchstone for the correctness of the T800 FPU. The microcode of the T800 FPU was documented in a restricted subset of occam.
